Then the line with slope containing the points $M$ and $N$ is
\begin{align*}
y-1=m(x-1)
\end{align*}
where $m$ is the slope. Since the two points are $(1,1)$ and $(\frac{11}{2},1)$, we can find $m$ by the formula
\begin{align*}
m=\frac{y_2-y_1}{x_2-x_1}=\frac{1-1}{(\frac{11}{2})-1}=\boxed{\frac{-2}{3}}.
